{
  "texts": [
    "Additional prompt engineering could improve the performance of ChatGPT-family models, such as developing prompts that provide details of the annotation guidelines as done by Ramachandran et al.",
    "This is an area for future study, especially once these models can be readily used with real clinical data.",
    "With additional prompt engineering and model refinement, performance of these models could improve in the future and provide a promising avenue to extract SDoH while reducing the human effort needed to label training datasets.",
    "It is well-documented that LMs learn the biases, prejudices, and racism present in the language they are trained on [35] [36] [37] [38].",
    "Thus, it is essential to evaluate how LMs could propagate existing biases, which in clinical settings could amplify the health disparities crisis [1] [2] [3]."
  ]
}